cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about deep learning architectures for semantic segmentation and dense image labeling, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes two encoder-decoder based networks, LRN and G-FRNet, which are both deep learning models that require training data and optimization, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces gate units to control information flow, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed models on several datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
